4. IMAGE GENERATION LOGIC (SMARTPHONE PROP & REVIEWER VIBE): 
   - STYLE DETECTION & LOGO FALLBACK (CRITICAL): Carefully analyze the [ATTACHED IMAGE]. 
     * If the image is a 3D animation/avatar, start the image prompt with "High quality 3D animation render, Pixar style, stylized 3D avatar". 
     * If it is a real human, start with "Authentic smartphone photo, photorealistic".
     * LOGO/OBJECT FALLBACK: If the image is a LOGO, typography, or an inanimate object (NO character present), you MUST randomly choose either a Real Human OR a 3D Animation style. Also, you MUST extract the dominant colors from the logo and apply them to the talent's clothing or background.
   - FRAMING: MUST use "Medium shot, waist-up framing" OR "Medium full shot".
   - MANDATORY PROP (SMARTPHONE/LAPTOP): The talent MUST be sitting or standing comfortably while holding a smartphone in their hand (as if reviewing an online shop) OR sitting at a desk with a laptop. 
   - BACKGROUND TRIGGER: Integrate the vibe of the [ATTACHED IMAGE]. Append "as aesthetic reference image" to the prompt so the AI adopts the color palette or vibe of the store.
   - BABY/KIDS STORE DETECTION: If the store is dedicated to baby, toddler, or kid products:
     * IMAGE SUBJECT: The image MUST feature a "Young Indonesian [mother/father] (25-30 years old) with a warm expression". 
     * COMPOSITION & PROP: The parent is seen interacting happily with a baby or toddler (e.g., holding the baby, or dressing the baby with items from the store). 
     * STABILITY constraint: The focus must remain clear on the adult's face.

5. SINGLE SCENE LTX FORMAT (STABLE CAMERA, REAL-TIME SPEED & LIP-SYNC): 
   - Generate a single "ltx_prompt" string. Remove all [visual] tags.
   - CAMERA DYNAMICS & ACTION (STRICTLY STABLE - LIP-SYNC PRIORITY): 
     * The camera MUST remain perfectly stable on a tripod throughout the entire video.
     * STRICTLY FORBIDDEN: DO NOT write any instructions for zooming in, pushing in, panning, turning the body, or dynamic camera movements. Keep the framing exactly as it started.
     * BODY INTERACTION: Describe the talent looking directly at the camera lens the ENTIRE time holding their smartphone. 
     * SPEED TRIGGERS: YOU MUST INCLUDE "talking with high energy, real-time normal speed, natural brisk movements". STRICTLY AVOID words like "gently", "slow", "smooth", or "minimal" to prevent unwanted slow-motion effects.
   - SPECIAL HANDLING FOR BABY/KIDS STORES:
     * LIP-SYNC ENFORCEMENT: Apply the real-time lip-sync and continuous mouth movement instructions ONLY to the adult parent talent. 
     * PASSIVE SUBJECT: The baby or child must remain a passive, happy subject (smiling, sleeping, or playing naturally), NOT talking to the camera.
